Set Push Notifications for Messaging for In-App

You can set push notifications for your iOS or Android mobile apps in your Messaging for In-App channel. Unlike messages that are automated or sent by agents, push notifications are temporary and don’t appear in a user’s messaging history.

This feature is available in Lightning Experience. To set up this feature, you need the Customize Application and Modify Metadata Through Metadata API Functions permissions.

Before setting up push notifications, review and prepare platform-specific information for iOS and Android devices. You also need access to Apple credentials for iOS and Firebase credentials for Android.

To configure push notifications, follow these steps:

1. From Setup, enter Embedded Service Deployments.
2. Select the deployment you want to use.
3. Click View next to Push Notifications.
4. Enter the required information for your push notifications by platform.

Required Fields for iOS:
* App Identifier
* APNS Host
* Key Identifier
* Team Identifier
* Signing Key

Required Fields for Android:
* Firebase Project Name
* Firebase Database URL
* Service Account JSON
title: Set Up Push Notifications for Messaging in Salesforce
